### requests.http - ready-made requests for every endpoint.
### Works in IntelliJ (open file, click the green arrow next to each request)
### or VS Code with the "REST Client" extension ("Send Request" link).
### Server must be running. PowerShell equivalents are in RUN-LOCAL.md.

### 0. Ping - simplest endpoint (and the rate-limit demo target)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/ping

### 1. List all tasks
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks

### 2. List only completed tasks
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks?completed=true

### 3. Get one task by id
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/1

### 4. Create a new task  (expect: 201 Created + Location header)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "My first POST request",
  "description": "Created straight from requests.http"
}

### 5. Update task 1  (PUT replaces title/description/completed)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Learn Spring Boot basics - DONE",
  "description": "Finished the notes",
  "completed": true
}

### 6. Delete task 2  (expect: 204 No Content)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/2

### 7. Validation error demo: blank title  (expect: 400 + fieldErrors)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "",
  "description": "This will be rejected"
}

### 8. Not-found demo  (expect: 404 JSON error)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/9999

### 9. RATE LIMIT demo: click request #0 six times fast.
### Requests 1-5 return 200 (burst capacity), the 6th returns 429 from
### YOUR TokenBucketStrategy. Wait a second -> one token refills -> 200 again.
GET http://localhost:8080/api/ping
